thread.title: Girls' Soccer: Wayne derby highlights PCT semifinal round

title: Girls' Soccer: Wayne derby highlights PCT semifinal round
text:
Buy this photo photo by jim alcorn STRAIGHT AHEAD - Cameron Santers, right, and teammate Gillian Brogna (17) lead the Patriots into Saturday's Passaic County Tournament semifinal round against crosstown rivals Wayne Valley. 
WAYNE - Imani Thompson's second-half double fired Wayne Valley into the semifinals of the Passaic County Coaches' Association girls' soccer tournament. 
Down a goal, Thompson helped rally the fourth-seeded Indians past rival DePaul Catholic, 3-2, last Saturday in the quarterfinals. 
It sets up a Wayne derby Saturday in the semifinals when the Indians host Wayne Hills at 4 p.m. 
With the score knotted at 2 in the final seven minutes, Thompson headed home the match-decider off the foot of Jen Cannarella. Wayne Valley's defense did the rest, squeezing DePaul, which clawed to grab an equalizer. 
Senior Brianna DeLuccia (four saves) was brilliant in goal, silencing the Spartans, who pushed for a two-goal edge. 
DePaul's Nine Lombardo and Gianna Rizzo helped the Spartans (4-5-1 overall) carry a 2-1 lead into the intermission. Victoria Carnevale and Alyssa Oviedo had assists. 
Randi Smith deposited her 16th goal of the campaign to halve the deficit at 2-1 before Thompson took over in the second half. Smith also turned facilitator on Thompson's equalizer midway through the second. 
DePaul's netminding tandem of Alli Hennion (two saves) and Rilee Keenan (three) combined for five saves. 
The Indians tuned up for the county date, overwhelming Eastside, 10-0, last Thursday in a Big North Conference interdivisional match in Paterson. 
Eight different players scored for the Indians, who led, 8-0, at the break. Randi Smith had two goals and an assist, Kayley Negast contributed a goal and three helpers and Jen Cannarella added a goal and two assists. 
Wayne Valley (7-4) is back at it with three matches in the Big North Independence, starting Thursday with Lakeland and then it's off to Passaic Valley on Tuesday. Both matches kick off at 4 p.m. The Indians opened the week on Oct. 13 with West Milford. 
Additionally, DePaul defeated an opponent for the second time within a week. 
Oviedo, one of the state's top sophomores, had a goal and assists to propel Big Green over West Milford, 2-1, last Thursday in an interdivisional contest. 
Oviedo tallied DePaul's second goal from the spot, proving to be the eventual winner. Earlier in the first half, Oviedo assisted on Carnevale's strike, which gave Big Green a 1-0 lead. 
Cristina Pellegrino evened the match at 1 midway through the opening half. 
Hennion (three saves) and Keenan (two) teamed for five saves while West Milford's Olivia DelColliano made 10 saves. 
The Spartans play host to Immaculate Heart Academy on Friday at 7 p.m. at Alumni Field. They opened the week on Tuesday against Holy Angels in the Big North United. 
Hills in semis 
Elsewhere, Wayne Hills is back in the county tournament semifinals. 
Last Saturday, the Patriots received goal apiece from three different players in a 3-0 blanking of Passaic County Technical Institute in the county quarterfinals. 
Deana Abdou, Gillian Brogna and Olivia Prusakowski netted strikes and Callen Vander May collected two assists. Wayne Hills improved to 8-2.
